    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013\nMason Edwards\nwas again dominant as the No. 13 USC baseball team tossed a two-hit shutout to open its series against Washington with a 5-0 win on Friday night.\nEdwards combined with\nGavin Lauridsen\nto hold the Huskies in check all night as USC moves to 22-1 overall and 6-1 in Big Ten play with the win. Washington falls to 9-12, 4-3.\nEdwards worked six scoreless innings while striking out a career-high 12 batters to move to 5-0 on the season. He gave up just one hit and three walks, allowing only one runner past first base in his first five innings of work. The lone spot of trouble for the junior lefty came in the sixth, as Washington got runners to second and third with two outs, but Edwards recorded his 12\nth\nstrikeout to strand them both.\nLauridsen entered the game with a 5-0 lead to start the seventh and kept the visiting Huskies off the board the rest of the way for his second save of the season. The freshman righty gave up just one hit and one walk while striking out four batters.\nThe Trojans opened the scoring in the third inning, getting a pair of runs on three Washington errors in the inning.\nAdrian Lopez\nand\nKevin Takeuchi\nthen doubled the lead in the fourth with RBI singles. Lopez tacked on a fifth run in the sixth inning, scoring\nAbbrie Covarrubias\nwith a sacrifice fly to make it 5-0.\nCovarrubias had two hits and scored three runs in the game, while Lopez led the way with three RBI.\nEdwards has now gone at least six innings and struck out 10 or more batters in each of his last five starts. For the season, he owns a 0.25 ERA, with 64 strikeouts, 14 walks and seven hits allowed.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nMason Edwards\n: 6.0 IP, H, 0R, 3BB, 12K\nGavin Lauridsen\n: 3.0 IP, H, 0R, BB, 4K\nAdrian Lopez\n: 2-for-3, 3 RBI\nAbbrie Covarrubias\n: 2-for-4, 3R\nCOMING UP\nThe Trojans and Huskies are back in action on Saturday night at 7 p.m. and then wrap things up on Sunday at 1 p.m. All USC home games will be broadcast on B1G+.\nHear from\n@MasonJEdwards\nafter another Friday night gem at Dedeaux \u270c\ufe0f\n#FightOn\nx\n@YETICoolers\npic.twitter.com/oLeKaDqtbn\n\u2014 USC Baseball (@USC_Baseball)\nMarch 21, 2026",
